Ben Benally is a Navajo who is from an area known as the Wild Ruins but now lives in Los Angeles. Benally, who believes he is related to Abel somehow, does his best to help Abel adjust to city life in Los Angeles when he first meets him on the job at the factory. The novel's third section, "The Night Chanter," is written primarily from Benally's point of view. The tone of his language paints a picture of Ben as a pragmatic and practical man who is aware of his Indian heritage but aspires to many of the amenities of the modern American lifestyle.